  <string name="learn_samatha_title">Samatha in Theravada context</string>
  <string name="learn_samatha_body">In Theravada practice, samatha refers to calm collectedness developed through steady attention and reduced agitation. It supports stability and clarity but is not identical to full liberating insight on its own.</string>
  <string name="learn_score_title">Samatha Score in this app</string>
  <string name="learn_score_body">Samatha Score is a training proxy. It combines normalized Relaxed Alertness Index with an optional artefact penalty for movement, contact instability, EMG proxy, blink/transient activity, and stalls.</string>
  <string name="learn_metric_difference_title">Samatha Score vs Relaxed Alertness Index</string>
  <string name="learn_metric_difference_body">Relaxed Alertness Index is the normalized EEG index (alpha versus high-frequency activity). Samatha Score starts from that index and then optionally applies artefact penalty. If artefact penalty is off, the two are effectively the same signal.</string>
  <string name="learn_caveat_title">Interpretation limits</string>
  <string name="learn_caveat_body">This score is not a direct measure of meditative attainment. It is a practical biofeedback estimate based on one dry frontal electrode and should be interpreted as a session aid, not as doctrinal validation.</string>
  <string name="learn_wellbeing_title">Wellbeing note</string>
  <string name="learn_wellbeing_body">SamathaScope is a non-medical training tool. If you feel discomfort, fatigue, or stress during sessions, pause and recover before continuing.</string>
  <string name="learn_sources_title">Sources</string>
  <string name="learn_sources_intro">The app includes short offline summaries and optional links for deeper reading.</string>
  <string name="learn_source_1">AN 11.2 (canonical reference)</string>
  <string name="learn_source_2">AN 4.41 (canonical reference)</string>
